erika burgess (born 1 october 1984 in new plymouth, new zealand) is a new zealand netball player. burgess plays for the southern steel in the anz championship, having previously played for the western flyers (2003â€“06) and southern sting (2007) in the national bank cup. a former member of the new zealand a squad, burgess made the extended training squad for the silver ferns, although has yet to make it into the senior team.